tickets.subject: Onboarding Provisioning - UPDATE - Zaria Teal - 94987 - 07-22-2025 - Access and Applications (see initial request in ticket 1951962) - Login/Access - Onboarding a New Hire

custom_fields.closure_notes:
Thank you for reaching out - access has been provided for this particular situation. 

For the future however, due to the high volume of requests for Epic access that our team receives every morning, and to ensure the team members that do not regularly work in your office are setup appropriately and ahead of time for the day when they come in to help, please submit a ticket requesting access as soon as you know they will be coming to your office. We would advise not waiting until the morning of, but submitting your request in advance as much as possible. 

In order for a new office or department to show up in Epic, a complete restart of the Epic application is needed. Please completely exit out of Hyperspace (if you are already logged in), close the program altogether,  and then log in again. The new department will be in your list of departments to select from, either at the login screen, or under the "Change Context" tab, after the initial login into Epic - remember to look under the "Search" tab, as opposed to the "Recent" tab. 

Have a wonderful day! :)
